tuple

typescript

(1) array with type-declaration for each index
    - and therefore, with a pre-defined length
(2) elems at indices may be named
    - purely informative

EXAMPLE
(1)
const ls : [number, string, boolean] = [1, "joe", false];
ls.push("mary")
console.log(ls); // [ 1, 'joe', false, 'mary' ]

(2)
const point : [x: number, y: number] = [1, 2];
